---------------------------------------------------11th Video----------------------------------------------------------
How Version works with package

semantic versioning
lodash: "4.16.1"

4 major version
16 minor version
1 patch version 

Change in functionality change the major versiion number
new feature added but this is not change any functionality then change in minor version
bug fix then patch version increment

if we want to install any specific version   - npm install lodash@3.3.0 --save
if we want to install latest patch with specific major & minor version   - npm install lodash@3.3 --save
if we want to install latest minor and patch with specific major version   - npm install lodash@3 --save

---------------------------------------------------12th Video----------------------------------------------------------
we can install any version we want 

we can add negation symbol before major version so the major and minor version will remain the same and afer running the npm install we can get the latest
version of the patch number.

mention in the lodash version "~4.16.21"

then run the npm install

---------------------------------------------------13th Video----------------------------------------------------------

How to Update the Package

it will update the lodash       - npm update lodash --save

it will update dev dependency      -  npm update --dev --save-dev  

 this will update all the dependency and packages     -  npm update

this will update all the global package            -  npm update -g

this will update a particular global package    -   npm update -g gulp

update the npm to globally upadted version -   npm install npm@latest -g

---------------------------------------------------14th Video----------------------------------------------------------

How npm Prune works

Basically it removes extraneous  Package that is not in package.json file but in the project folder

we can check it like which package is extraneous.

npm list --depth 0

we can remove using npm prune

---------------------------------------------------15th Video----------------------------------------------------------

Some Shortcurts for NPM

we can reduce the npm codes to-    npm init -yes to npm init -y
this above command is used to create package.json with deafult values without asking any questions

we can reduce the codes of install comand of     -npm install lodash    to    npm i lodash

we can reduce the codes of save install comand of  -   npm install lodash -save  to    npm i lodash -S

we can reduce the codes of install for devtols like - npm install moment --save-dev   to  npm i moment -D

npm -global to npm -g

we can find more shorthands/shortcut key in   -   https://docs.npmjs.com/cli/v8/using-npm/config

---------------------------------------------------16th Video----------------------------------------------------------

npm Scripts topic
How to run npm Scripts

enter the value in test under scripts change the value to start then assign the start point of you project then open the cmd/terminal
run the command npm start then the files start executing.

